In the Matter of the Claim of Joe Green, Appellant. Philip Ross, as Industrial Commissioner, Respondent. Submitted January 31, 1977; decided February 15, 1977

Reported below, 54 AD2d 1049.

Motion for leave to appeal dismissed upon the ground that movant is not aggrieved by the determination at the Appellate Division (CPLR 5511; Cohen and Karger, Powers of the New York Court of Appeals, §91, p 395; Matter of Zaiac, 279 NY 545, 554).
